        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Federal Initiative To Guarantee Health by Targeting Fentanyl Act</strong></p> <p>This bill places fentanyl-related substances as a class into schedule I of the Controlled Substances Act. A schedule I controlled substance is a drug, substance, or chemical that has a high potential for abuse; has no currently accepted medical value; and is subject to regulatory controls and administrative, civil, and criminal penalties under the Controlled Substances Act.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
